===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{Han compound|刀|幺|t1=knife|t2=silk|ls=ic|nocap=y}} or {{Han compound|刀|𢆶|t1=knife|t2=silk|ls=ic|nocap=y}} — to cut silk threads.

Now {{Han compound|糸|刀|卪|c1=s|c2=s|c3=p|alt1=糹|alt3=巴 (卪)|t1=silk|t2=knife|ls=psc|nocap=y|no_och=y|no_och3=y}}.

Most likely unrelated to [[色]].

===Etymology===
Compare {{cog|my|ဆွတ်|t=to pluck}} ({{zh-ref|Hill, 2019}}).

